<div class="tip-card">💧 <strong>Big Water Bag:</strong> the local item doc describes it as an <strong>8-use / 8-liter</strong> bag. <strong>Right-click a water block</strong> to fill it; if it contains dirty water, a furnace cleans it in about <strong>30 seconds</strong>.</div>
<p><strong>Elemental Water Bag</strong> (via mercury) is a Knowledge-Book-gated 16-liter mercury conversion of the Big Water Bag. The <strong>Adamantium Water Bag</strong> also reaches 16 liters, so this is better treated as a separate advanced recipe path rather than a higher-capacity final tier.</p>
<div class="tip-card">☿ <strong>Elemental Water Bag via mercury:</strong> the local item doc says it is made by putting <strong>1 Big Water Bag + 1 Ancient Metal Ingot</strong> into a <strong>full cauldron of liquefied mercury</strong>. The conversion takes about <strong>30 seconds</strong> with magma/lava heat below, and dirty water is still purified in a furnace in about <strong>120 seconds</strong>.</div>
<div class="info-box">💧 <strong>Water-source trick:</strong> the local item docs show that bucket water handling goes beyond simple pouring. With <strong>Ctrl + right-click</strong>, you can spend <strong>100 XP</strong> to place a <strong>permanent water source</strong>; normal pouring still creates only temporary flowing water.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🥣 <strong>Pure Water Bowl / Hot Water:</strong> the local item docs say <strong>Bowl + right-click on a freshwater lake</strong> gives a <strong>Pure Water Bowl</strong>, restoring <strong>8 thirst</strong>. You can heat that into <strong>Hot Water</strong> in a furnace to help relieve <strong>heat stroke</strong>, and after about <strong>3 minutes</strong> it cools back into a Pure Water Bowl.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🧪 <strong>Wooden Water Filter:</strong> it <strong>needs Filter Paper</strong> and can purify up to <strong>9 liters</strong> at once. Dirty water goes into the <strong>top</strong> section, clean water collects in the <strong>bottom</strong>, and <strong>Shift-right-click</strong> with an empty container on the upper/lower half pulls out dirty/clean water. If you place an infinite water source above it, it auto-feeds itself.</div>
<div class="info-box">🛢️ <strong>Fluid Tank:</strong> it can store water, purified water, milk, magma, and liquefied gold. Placed under a water filter, it can automatically collect the finished clean water. If the tank is broken, the stored liquid is <strong>lost</strong>. Local doc capacities: <strong>Copper/Silver 20 L</strong>, <strong>Gold 30 L</strong>, <strong>Iron 40 L</strong>, <strong>Hardstone 50 L</strong>, <strong>Ancient Metal 60 L</strong>, <strong>Mithril 70 L</strong>, <strong>Adamantium 80 L</strong>.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🧻 <strong>Filter Paper:</strong> right-click with it while <strong>not sneaking</strong> to insert it into the filter. The local item doc gives it <strong>36 durability</strong>, and <strong>1 durability filters 1 liter</strong> of clean water. The wooden filter itself <strong>cannot be picked up with Shift-right-click</strong>, and is only properly broken by an <strong>axe</strong>.</div>
<div class="info-box">🧻 <strong>Advanced filter papers in v0.9.0:</strong> based on the local advanced-filter doc plus the generated recipe set, the old full upgrade ladder is no longer the practical current route. The reliably active craftable line is <strong>standard</strong>, <strong>Gold Filter Paper (50 durability)</strong>, and <strong>Ancient Metal Filter Paper (62 durability)</strong>.</div>

